The paper describes a tool for gaining new knowledge from unstructured text data using Formal Concept Analysis (FCA), Emergent Self Organizing Maps (ESOM) and Hidden Markov Models (HMM). These techniques are commonly used in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), information retrieval (cs.IR), machine learning (cs.LG), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and social and information networks (cs.SI). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
